                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.135,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has our opinion this morning in case 13-1421, Bank of America v. Caulkett and the consolidated case."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.135,
                        "stop": 191.76,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.135,
                                "stop": 20.132,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "These consolidated cases come to us on writs of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.132,
                                "stop": 27.547,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The debtors in these cases, respondents here, each have two mortgage liens on their homes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.547,
                                "stop": 31.875,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Petitioner Bank of America holds the junior liens on each."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.875,
                                "stop": 41.08,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "These liens are wholly underwater, that is to say, each debtor owes more on a senior lien than his home is worth."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.08,
                                "stop": 46.583,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Thus if the homes were sold today the bank would get nothing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.583,
                                "stop": 65.614,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The debtors each filed for Chapter 7 bankruptcy and moved to void the junior mortgage liens under Section 506(d) of the Bankruptcy Code. In each case the Bankruptcy Court granted the motion and the District Court and the Eleventh Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.614,
                                "stop": 71.623,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today, we reversed the judgments of the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.623,
                                "stop": 100.228,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Section 506(d) provides that a lien is void \u201cto the extent that it secures a claim against the debtor that is not an allowed secured claim.\u201d Thus, the debtor here may void the bank\u0027s junior mortgage liens only if the bank\u0027s claim or right to repayment is not an allowed secured claim because there is no dispute that the bank\u0027s claims are allowed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.228,
                                "stop": 104.884,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The only question before us is whether they are secured."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.884,
                                "stop": 118.613,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Although the code itself suggests that the bank\u0027s claims are not secured, this Court has already adopted reading of the term secured claim that forecloses this conclusion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.613,
                                "stop": 142.314,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In Dewsnup v. Timm, this Court construed the term secured claim to include any claim secured by a lien and fully allowed pursuant to Section 502. Because the bank\u0027s claims here are secured by liens and allowed pursuant to Section 502, they cannot be voided under Dewsnup."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.314,
                                "stop": 157.118,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The debtors have not asked us to overrule Dewsnup, but instead have asked us to limit that decision to partially underwater mortgage liens as opposed to wholly underwater mortgage liens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.118,
                                "stop": 164.302,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We decline to adopt this artificial distinction and there is little support for that view in the code."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.302,
                                "stop": 171.4,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these reasons and others set forth in our opinion we reverse the judgments of the Eleventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.4,
                                "stop": 174.246,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 174.246,
                                "stop": 182.397,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice and Justices Scalia, Ginsburg, Alito and Kagan joined the opinion in full."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.397,
                                "stop": 191.76,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justices Kennedy, Breyer and Sotomayor would join all of the opinion except for the one footnote."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
